sections.text:
• Sunnybank, Queensland, a suburb in Brisbane, Queensland, Australia much reduced in size from the previous suburb of Sunnybank
  • Electoral district of Sunnybank, Queensland, Australia
  • Town of Sunnybank, a former town that was absorbed into the City of Brisbane
  • Sunnybank, Aberdeen, an area of Aberdeen at the eastern end of Kittybrewster, just south of Old Aberdeen

• Sunnybank (Hot Springs, North Carolina), listed on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina
  • Sunnybank Kennels, founded by writer and dog breeder Albert Payson Terhune, author of Lad, A Dog and many other books about Sunnybank Kennels and dogs in general
